 Port Elizabeth - A 29-year-old male suspect was arrested on Monday afternoon and a prohibited and unlicenced firearm recovered with 12 rounds of live ammunition. "This followed after SAPS Flying Squad members saw a white Suzuki Swift vehicle offloading a male passenger on the intersection of the M17 and M19 between Motherwell and Kwazakele," said police spokesperson, Captain Andre Beetge. "When the police were spotted, the Suzuki made a speedy getaway, but the male that got off was arrested. "In his possession a 9mm pistol (with serial number removed) was found with 12 rounds of ammunition." Capt Beetge said that he was charged for the possession of a prohibited and unlicensed fire arm and ammunition. "He will be appearing before the Motherwell Magistrate's Court on Tuesday." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  